doc.after: Carabane has many historic sites, such as the Catholic mission house built in 1880 which has since been turned into a hotel, a Brittany-style church building which is no longer in use, and a former slave-trade building. There is also a French cemetery where a Troupes de marine-Captain with the name Aristide Protet was shot with a poisoned arrow and buried standing up in front of the sea, according to his last wishes.[128] Some tour guides falsely claim that this was Auguste LÃ©opold Protet,[129] the founder of the city of Dakar, but the name Aristide Protet is clearly shown on the tomb's plaque.[130]
